observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed that the:
General Service Office:
11immediately implement and consistently maintain stock cards for all inventory items;
12establish a process for preparing and regularly utilizing the Report of Supplies and Materials Issued Summary. This report provides a summary of inventory issues, which is needed for reconciling inventory balances and identifying discrepancies; and the use of the Report of Supplies and Materials Issued Summary and shall be submitted to the Municipal Accounting Office on a regular basis.
13adopt the Weighted Average Method for Inventory Valuation.
Municipal Accounting Office:
14implement the Weighted Average Method for valuation, rather than purchase order prices;
15implement a system to record inventory items as issued only upon actual consumption, rather than at the time of purchase and established a flow-chart schedule and to be introduced to all processing personnel of the agency;
16implement and consistently maintain subsidiary ledger cards for all inventory items to ensure they provide detailed records of inventory movements, supporting the control and accuracy of inventory balances.

We recommended that Management direct the following departments to expedite the disposal of unserviceable properties in accordance with COA Circular No. 92-386:
1. The General Service Office will conduct the inspection of the reported unserviceable properties and prepare the corresponding IIRUP thereon, after which, proceed with the disposal procedures in accordance with COA Circular No. 92-386 dated October 20, 1992 – “Prescribing Rules and Regulations on Supply and Property Management in the Local Government”;
2. The Municipal Treasurer's Office will process the IIRUP for disposal of unserviceable properties and submit it to the Accounting Office and COA Office in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006 and Section 79 of PD No. 1445;
3. The Office of the Municipal Accountant shall draw necessary journal entries to derecognize from the books of accounts the book value of the disposed properties from the receipt of properly accomplished and approved IIRUP from the GSO as the basis.
